In package.json we can write custom script to execute in terminal like this app was running using - "npx parcel index.html" this can be configured inside package.json - scripts as "start":"parcel index.html"

JSX is HTML like syntax/ more like XML like, NOT HTML JSX is different than React, is not part of React. It's used with React for ease of readability.

JSX is not directly understood by Browsers or React or JS Engine, it is first transpiled to make it understandable to React/ JS engine. This transpilation is done by Babel(JS Package), whiich in turn is managed by Parcel.\

Babel transpiles the JSX code into React.createElement, that's why if a element is created using React.createElement and using JSX, both are same.
JSX(Babel transpiles) => React.createElement => ReactElement-JS(Object) => HTML Element (via ReactDOM's render method)

Babel is a transpiler/ JavaScript compiler.

JSX attribute tag are written in camel-Case. JSX written across multiple lines needs to be wrapped by () for Babel to understand.

REACT Components
2 types of components:
i) Class Based Components - OLD method
ii) Functional Componenets - NEW

React Functional Component

- A function that returns a JSX. OR A JavaScript function which returns a React element(JSX).
- Functional Components should always have their first letter of name in capital.

Component Composition - Using multiple components inside a component OR a mix of components
